          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " High efficiency, good resolution NaI",
                " spectrometer (NaI(Tl) crystal, 25 cm in diameter",
                " and 30 cm long, surrounded by 11.4-cm-thick annulus",
                " and disk of NE102 plastic scintillator ehich served",
                " as an anticoincidence shield)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Differential cross sections for the elastic scattering",
                " of tagged, monochromatic photons have been measured",
                " for targets of carbon and calcium between 19 and 52",
                " MeV.",
                "The formalism for the interpretation of these cross",
                " sections in terms of the total photoabsorpion cross",
                " section and its partitioning into E1 and E2 parts was",
                " presented. For carbon, the excellent agreement has",
                " been found between the photoabsorption deduced from",
                " the scattering and previous direct measurements. The",
                " fore-to-aft asymmetries in the cross sections indicate",
                " that the bulk of E2 strength is about 50 MeV and not",
                " between 30 and 45 MeV, as previously thought. For",
                " calcium, the scattering data indicate that the",
                " integrated photoabsorption cross sections per nucleon",
                " are closer to the nearly constant value reported for",
                " A > 100 than previously thought. No compact E2",
                " strenght exhausting more than 0.5 classical sums was",
                " found below 50 MeV, although weaker or less compact",
                " strength cannot be ruled out."
              ]
            }
          ],
